The paper deals with information inequalities and entropy regions, which are topics typically studied in information theory (cs.IT). The use of duality and polymatroids suggests a connection to combinatorics and optimization (cs.CC), while the analysis of the entropy region involves mathematical properties of sets and functions (cs.DS). The study of information inequalities also has applications in cryptography and security (cs.CR), and the use of entropy as a measure of uncertainty is relevant to machine learning and data analysis (cs.SI).
